<subSubSection id="C3466570486D975AFF2DFBB999301531" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE336FB486D975AFF2DFBB999301531" blockId="17.[192,1440,1027,1115]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="B928EAE9486D975AFF2DFBB99B681571" bold="true" box="[192,328,1027,1051]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13672A7E486D975AFEBBFBB99B8D1571" box="[342,429,1027,1051]" captionStart="Figure 47-58" captionStartId="13.[192,276,1825,1847]" captionTargetBox="[192,1443,192,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-15@13.[192,1443,192,1797]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 47-58. Habiti. 47) Amboakis ampla. 48) A. antegalba. 49) A. diffusa. 50) Amboakis demagna. 51) A. waodani. 52) Epiphloeus erwini. 53) Madoniella aspera. 54) Madoniella darlingtoni. 55). Madoniella divida. 56) Madoniella spilota. 57) Plocamocera clinata. 58) P. lena." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352840/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
): In the key of madoniellan species (Opitz, in press), the 
<typeStatus id="54E78859486D975AFBBCFBB99EE01571" box="[1105,1216,1027,1051]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Holotype</typeStatus>
extends to couplet 11(4'), which accommodates 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D78486D975AFDCEFB99998B1551" authority="Opitz. From" authorityName="Opitz. From" box="[547,939,1059,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Madoniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubida">
<emphasis id="B928EAE9486D975AFDCEFB99992C1551" box="[547,780,1059,1083]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Madoniella rubida</emphasis>
Opitz. From
</taxonomicName>
the latter, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D78486D975AFBD7FB9E9E971551" authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2010" box="[1082,1207,1059,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Madoniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spilota">
<emphasis id="B928EAE9486D975AFBD7FB9E9E731551" box="[1082,1107,1060,1083]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B928EAE9486D975AFB8EFB999E971551" box="[1123,1207,1059,1083]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">spilota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens may be distinguished by the spotted condition of the legs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3466570486D975AFF2DFB399B721491" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE336FB486D975AFF2DFB399B861431" blockId="17.[192,1441,1155,1371]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="B928EAE9486D975AFF2DFB399B4C15F1" bold="true" box="[192,364,1155,1179]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B928EAE9486D975AFE9AFB3E9B8A15F1" box="[375,426,1156,1179]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Size</emphasis>
: Length 
<quantity id="4CA49B1E486D975AFDFAFB39985515F1" box="[535,629,1155,1179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="4.8">4.8 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity id="4CA49B1E486D975AFD21FB39990A15F1" box="[716,810,1155,1179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B928EAE9486D975AFCD9FB399E0215F1" box="[820,1058,1155,1179]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Integumental Color</emphasis>
: Cranium dark reddish-brown; pronotal disc dark brown, more reddish at sides; elytral disc with well-developed insignia, posterolateral extensions of posterior block missing, posterocentral extension of posterior block broadly confluent with yellow macula on elytral apex. 
<emphasis id="B928EAE9486D975AFDC0FB59984E1591" box="[557,622,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Head</emphasis>
: Vertex narrower than eyes in head dorsal view; antenna as depicted in figure 11. 
<emphasis id="B928EAE9486D975AFEB1FAB99B951471" box="[348,437,1283,1307]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotal side margins very sinuous, anterior margin arcuate plane; elytral form oblong; elytral punctations large; anterior margin of protibia with 5 spines. 
<emphasis id="B928EAE9486D975AFB99FA999EC81451" box="[1140,1256,1315,1339]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Aedeagus not available for study.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE336FB486D975AFF2DFA3998A814F1" blockId="17.[192,648,1411,1435]" box="[192,648,1411,1435]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
