One specimen examined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE336FB486D975AFF2DFA799B721491" blockId="17.[192,1440,1473,1531]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="B928EAE9486D975AFF2DFA799B8314B1" bold="true" box="[192,419,1475,1499]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Natural History.</emphasis>
The primary 
<typeStatus id="54E78859486D975AFDA2FA7E98A514B6" box="[591,645,1476,1500]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">type</typeStatus>
was collected at 
<quantity id="4CA49B1E486D975AFCBCFA79998B14B1" box="[849,939,1475,1499]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" unit="m" value="1850.0">1850 m</quantity>
sometime between October 29 
<superScript id="7C299BB3486D975AFAF2FA7B9F0E14A5" attach="left" box="[1311,1326,1473,1487]" fontSize="6" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">th</superScript>
and September 18 
<superScript id="7C299BB3486D975AFED6FA5B9B6A1485" attach="none" box="[315,330,1505,1519]" fontSize="6" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">th</superScript>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
